definitions.definition: (of a statement) Arousing doubt; questionable; open to suspicion.
definitions.example: After he made some dubious claims about the company, fewer people trusted him.

definitions.definition: (of a person) In disbelief; wavering, uncertain, or hesitating in opinion; inclined to doubt; undecided.
definitions.example: She was dubious about my plan at first, but later I managed to persuade her to cooperate.
